## When to use this component 

You should use the ONS header at the top of any ONS service.

## How to use this component

### External header
{{
    patternlibExample({ "path": "components/header/examples/external-basic/index.njk" })
}}

The external header should be used across public facing services.

### Internal
{{
    patternlibExample({ "path": "components/header/examples/internal-basic/index.njk" })
}}
The internal service variant of the header. Use the modifier `header---internal header--thin` when implementing for an internal service. 

### External with description
{{
    patternlibExample({ "path": "components/header/examples/external-hero/index.njk" })
}}

Allows for text to be added below the title by adding the `header--hero` modifier class to the header element. This should be used when the service would benefit from a description which informs users of what the service provides.

### External with navigation
{{
    patternlibExample({ "path": "components/header/examples/external-navigation/index.njk" })
}}

For services that require a main navigation. For mobile users, a menu button is shown which allows the navigation menu to be open and closed using javascript. 

